Having regard to the Treaty establishing the European Community,
Having regard to Council Regulation (EEC) No 1785/81 of 30 June 1981 on the common organization of the markets in the sugar sector (1), as last amended by the Act of Accession of Austria, Finland and Sweden, and in particular Article 19 (7) thereof,
Whereas Commission Regulation (EC) No 3115/94 of 20 December 1994 amending Annexes I and II to Council Regulation (EEC) No 2658/87 on the tariff and statistical nomenclature and on the Common Customs Tariff (2) provides for an amendment as regards  inulin syrup;
Whereas, following the amendment of Article 1 (2) of Regulation (EEC) No 1785/81, inulin syrup may, pursuant to Article 19 (2) of that Regulation, be eligible for an export refund; whereas it is therefore necessary, in order to be able to distinguish  refunds for inulin syrup, to amend the product nomenclature contained in the Annex to Commission Regulation (EEC) No 3846/87 (3), as last amended by Regulation (EC) No 3333/94 (4);
Whereas the measures provided for in this Regulation are in accordance with the opinion of the Management Committee for Sugar,
